==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skewer
<hw>Skew"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably of Scand,
origin; cf. Sw. & Dan. <ets>skifer</ets> a slate. Cf. <er>Shuver</er> a
fragment.]</ety> <def>A pin of wood or metal for fastening meat to a
spit, or for keeping it in form while roasting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Meat well stuck with <qex>skewers</qex> to make it look round.</q>
<rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skewer</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Skewer
<hw>Skew"er</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Skewered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Skewering</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To fasten with
skewers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ski</ent>⟦br⟧
